## ping
Ping works using the ICMP protocol,The ICMP protocol works on the Network layer of the OSI Model
to change the interval of sent ping requests: -i
to restrict requests to IPv4: -4
a more verbose output: -v
## traceroute
The logical follow-up to the ping command is traceroute. Traceroute can be used to map the path your request takes as it heads to the lab machine.
-i for interface
-T for tcp syn request
